author: Inside Edition
description: Robert Hocevar was arrested during a police raid at his home outside Cleveland, Ohio. For years, police say, Hocevar had been terrorizing women. He was a video security systems installer and was accused of using his access to victims' homes and businesses to spy on them. Julie Runyon says she and her co-workers started receiving disturbing calls and text messages from a stranger while they were at work bartending. Hocevar was convicted of stalking seven women.
title: Video Security Camera Installer Convicted of Stalking Women

author: Inside Edition
description: A family member of Charlie Kirk's alleged assassin Tyler Robinson recognized him from photos released by the FBI, and his father and a youth minister from his church turned him in. President Donald Trump was the first to break news on “Fox and Friends” on Friday morning. Authorities say Robinson drove to Utah Valley University, arriving at 8:29 a.m. After assassinating Kirk, the FBI says Robinson ran across the roof, jumped off, and fled the campus.
title: Tyler Robinson Turned In By Family: Authorities

author: Inside Edition
description: 22-year-old Tyler Robinson has been accused of the political assassination that is shocking the nation. Inside Edition spoke with criminologist Casey Jordan. Robinson was raised in a $600,000 six-bedroom home with hunting trophies on the walls. Social media posts show family vacations and fishing trips. In a news conference, authorities said Robinson's family members said he had become more political in recent years.
title: Who Is Charlie Kirk's Alleged Assassin Tyler Robinson?

author: Inside Edition
description: The term "civil war" went from being used 18,000 times a day to 129,000 times on X after Charlie Kirk's assassination. Utah's governor Spencer Cox warned the public about a campaign of disinformation on social media. Meanwhile, six historically Black campuses were placed on lockdown after being targeted by hoax threat calls. Former FBI agent Richard Frankel spoke with Inside Edition. Several groups have taken responsibility.
title: Authorities Report Staggering Uptick In Violent Threats

author: Inside Edition
description: Denise Richards' estranged husband Aaron Phyphers showed Inside Edition the shocking conditions at their rented home in California.
title: Exclusive Look Inside Denise Richards’ House of Squalor #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Scientists are issuing warnings about something that's not necessarily new, but relatively unknown. It's called Chagas Disease, and it's spread through what are known as kissing bugs. Researchers say it's been around for a long time. It can cause mild flu-like symptoms at first, but it is potentially deadly. Cases have been reported in eight states. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Scientists Warn About Chagas Disease Spread by Kissing Bugs

author: Inside Edition
description: Two American travel influencers tried to deboard after learned they were on the wrong flight. But they were out of luck.
title: American Travelers Realize They're Headed to Tunis, not Nice #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: A suspect is in custody in the shooting death of Charlie Kirk. Tyler Robinson, a 22-year-old southern Utah man, reportedly confessed to the shooting to his father. President Trump broke the news that authorities had a suspect in custody during a live interview with "Fox & Friends." Conservative activist Kirk was fatally struck in the neck with a bullet Wednesday while speaking at an event at Utah Valley University.
title: Charlie Kirk Shooting Suspect In Custody Is 22-Year-Old Tyler Robinson

author: Inside Edition
description: INSIDE EDITION set out to answer the question: Would your dog pick you over his food if an intruder broke into your home? We enlisted the help of professional guard dog experts Mike D’Abruzza and Nate Bonilla to put three New York dogs to the test. With their owner’s consent, we gave each dog a bowl of food, then had one of our experts come through the door acting as a home invader to see if they’d rescue their owner or finish their dinner.
title: Would Your Dog Pick You Over Its Dinner During a Home Invasion?

author: Inside Edition
description: A car chase came to an end in Los Angeles when deputies used a PIT maneuver to stop the fleeing vehicle. KCBS watched the pursuit from the sky and reported that deputies were chasing an allegedly stolen Range Rover with two people inside. The maneuver spun the car around and it ended up on the curb. Both suspects were taken into custody. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: PIT Maneuver Stops Suspected Stolen Car

author: Inside Edition
description: An SUV broke through the front window of a jewelry store in San Jose, California, and a group of thieves invaded it. They shoved the 88-year-old store owner, who suffered a stroke.
title: Thieves' SUV Smashed Through Jewelry Store Window #shorts
